--- a/resources/js/pages/users/UsersPage.vue
+++ b/resources/js/pages/users/UsersPage.vue
@@ DESCRIPTION
  This patch demonstrates adding permission guards to the UsersPage.vue
  "Bulk Deactivate" button which currently lacks a v-if permission check.
  
  The button at lines ~655-662 is disabled only by `!selectedIds.length || bulkLoading`
  but has no `v-if` based on canEditUsers permission. Any user viewing the page
  can see (and attempt to click) the Bulk Deactivate button.

  BEFORE:
    <button
      :disabled="!selectedIds.length || bulkLoading"
      @click="bulkDeactivate"
      class="..."
    >
      Bulk Deactivate
    </button>

  AFTER:
    <button
      v-if="canEditUsers"
      :disabled="!selectedIds.length || bulkLoading"
      @click="bulkDeactivate"
      class="..."
    >
      Bulk Deactivate
    </button>

--- Similar pattern for other pages ---

--- a/resources/js/pages/clients/ClientsListingPage.vue
+++ b/resources/js/pages/clients/ClientsListingPage.vue
@@ DESCRIPTION
  ClientsListingPage.vue has NO client-side permission guards.
  Import CSV, Export CSV, and Add New Client buttons are always visible.

  FIX: Add these computed properties to <script setup>:

    const auth = useAuthStore()
    const isSuperAdmin = computed(() => (auth.user?.roles ?? []).includes('superadmin'))
    const perms = computed(() => auth.user?.permissions ?? [])
    const canCreate = computed(() => isSuperAdmin.value || perms.value.includes('accounts.create') || perms.value.includes('accounts.edit'))
    const canImport = computed(() => isSuperAdmin.value || perms.value.includes('accounts.create'))
    const canExport = computed(() => isSuperAdmin.value || perms.value.includes('accounts.export_client_data'))

  Then wrap buttons:
    <button v-if="canImport" ...>Import CSV</button>
    <button v-if="canExport" ...>Export CSV</button>
    <button v-if="canCreate" ...>Add New Client</button>

--- a/resources/js/pages/dsp-tracker/DSPTrackerListingPage.vue
+++ b/resources/js/pages/dsp-tracker/DSPTrackerListingPage.vue
@@ DESCRIPTION
  CRITICAL: DSPTrackerListingPage.vue has ZERO permission guards.
  Delete Old File and Upload CSV buttons are always visible/clickable.

  FIX: Add these computed properties to <script setup>:

    const auth = useAuthStore()
    const isSuperAdmin = computed(() => (auth.user?.roles ?? []).includes('superadmin'))
    const perms = computed(() => auth.user?.permissions ?? [])
    const canUpload = computed(() => isSuperAdmin.value || perms.value.includes('dsp_tracker.upload_csv'))
    const canDelete = computed(() => isSuperAdmin.value || perms.value.includes('dsp_tracker.delete_existing_csv'))

  Then wrap buttons:
    <button v-if="canDelete" ...>Delete Old File</button>
    <button v-if="canUpload" ...>Upload CSV</button>

--- a/resources/js/pages/employees/EmployeesListingPage.vue
+++ b/resources/js/pages/employees/EmployeesListingPage.vue
@@ DESCRIPTION
  CRITICAL: canForceLogout is referenced but NEVER defined.
  Bulk Activate/Deactivate buttons lack v-if permission guards.

  FIX 1: Define the missing variable in <script setup>:

    const canForceLogout = computed(() =>
      isSuperAdmin.value || (auth.user?.permissions ?? []).includes('force_logout')
    )

  FIX 2: Add permission guards to bulk buttons:

    const canManageEmployees = computed(() =>
      isSuperAdmin.value || (auth.user?.permissions ?? []).includes('users.edit')
    )

    <button v-if="canManageEmployees" ...>Bulk Deactivate</button>
    <button v-if="canManageEmployees" ...>Bulk Activate</button>

